	<text xml:lang="la">
		<body>
			<div xml:id="div1" corresp="regest1">
				<p>
					<s n="1" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Gratiam et vitę innocentiam a patre et domino nostro Iesu Christo.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="2" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Nisi christianissimus d. Chuonradus <persName ref="person165">Pellicanus</persName> proximis nundinis Francfordiensibus<note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote" n="1">Die <placeName ref="place361">Frankfurter</placeName> Herbstmesse fand in der Regel zwischen 15. August und 8. September statt; vgl. HBBW VI <ref target="file10925">[Nr. 884]</ref>, S. 406, Anm. 5.</note> ad me litteras plenas pietate et fide misisset<note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote" n="2">Der nicht erhaltene Brief, am 31. August 1538 geschrieben, war am 27. Oktober bei <persName ref="person166">Pergener</persName> eingetroffen, wie aus dem unten Anm. 6 verzeichneten Schreiben hervorgeht.</note>, maxima adfectus essem tristitia; incertus plane fuissem litteras meas<note xml:id="fn3" type="footnote" n="3">HBBW VIII, <ref target="file11154">Nr. 1111</ref>.</note> quantumlibet impolitas Tigurum non pervenisse.</s>
					<s n="3" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Nunc autem recepi animum atque gaudio suffundor tam celebres viros infirmorum quoque fratrum habere rationem.</s>
					<s n="4" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Certi sumus ex omnibus vestris scriptis, quę nobis indicant summam mansuetudinem, pietatem et amorem christianum et nos vobis curę esse.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="5" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Nolo te ignorare, charissime Bulingere, te magnam iniisse gratiam cum illis etiam, qui hostes erant renate evangelistę[!] veritati, eo quod d. <persName ref="person779">Erasmum</persName> Roterod[amum] de pietate et litteris bene meritum scribis virum immortali laurea dignum; nam ea verba, que sincere de illo scribis li[bro] 2.</s>
					<s n="6" xml:lang="la" type="auto">De scripturę sanctę authoritate<note xml:id="fn4" type="footnote" n="4">Siehe De scripturae sanctae authoritate Zürich (<persName ref="person891">Froschauer</persName>) 1538 (HBBibl I 111). fol. 83r.</note> etc., ad multos etiam papisticę factionis perscripsi.</s>
					<s n="7" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Laudant et ipsi vestram modestiam ubique in scribendo; multis displicuit, quod a nonnullis apellaretur <persName ref="person1547">Lutianus</persName><note xml:id="fn5" type="footnote" n="5"><persName ref="person1547">Lukian von Samosata</persName> (als Inbegriff des gottlosen Spötters).</note>, <persName ref="person775">Epicurus</persName>, scepticus et aliis odiosis nominibus<note xml:id="fn6" type="footnote" n="6">Vgl. Luther, De servo arbitrio, WA XVIII 605, 27-32; 609, 21f.</note>.</s>
					<s n="8" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Sed tu, sincerissime in Christo frater, perge nos, qui longe a vobis sumus dissiti, instituere tuis sanctissimis scriptis.</s>
					<s n="9" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Dici non potest, quantum ea scripta, quę ex Tiguro, <placeName ref="place97">Basilea</placeName> vel <placeName ref="place1049">Argentorato</placeName> mittuntur, pios delectent; testes complures adducere possem.</s>
					<s n="10" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Reliqua ad d. Chuonradum<pb type="edition" next="64"/> <persName ref="person165">Pellicanum</persName> scripsi<note xml:id="fn7" type="footnote" n="7">Siehe <persName ref="person166">Pergener</persName> an <persName ref="person165">Konrad Pellikan</persName>, 21. Februar 1539; Autograph in: Zürich ZB, Ms F 47, 28.</note> et partim Germanice<note xml:id="fna" type="footnote" n="a"><hi>in der Vorlage</hi> Germanicae.</note> ad Christopherum <persName ref="person891">Froschouerum</persName><note xml:id="fn8" type="footnote" n="8">Nicht erhalten.</note>.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="11" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Vale semper in Christo cum omnibus tuis simmistis et tota ecclesia.</s>
					<s n="12" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Orate deum pro nobis.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="13" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Zittę, 21. die mensis februarii anno etc. 1539.</s>
					<s n="14" xml:lang="la" type="auto"><persName ref="person166">Osvaldus Pergenerus</persName>, tui deditissimus.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note type="address">[Adresse auf der Rückseite:]</note>
					<s n="15" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Summe pietatis et doctrinę viro d. Henricho Bulingero, <persName ref="person84">Tigurine</persName> ecclesię ministro fidelissimo, amico et fratri colendissimo.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
